# ClickUp Comment Style

Apply this guide before any `clickup_create_task_comment` or comment edit via MCP. If the user
passes raw content, expand it to this style. Do not invent technical data: if a commit / doc URL /
example ID is missing, ask or leave an explicit placeholder.

## What comment_text renders (verified live)

Renders (use):
- Inline code with backticks: `get_customer_orders` → displays as code.
- Raw URL: https://... → auto-linked.

Does NOT render — appears LITERAL:
- `**bold**`, `*italic*`, `~~strike~~`, `[text](url)`
- `##`/`###` headers, `-`/`*` bullets, `1.` lists, `>` blockquote, fences

Native formatting (headers/bold/code-block) lives in the `comment` ops array, which the MCP
does not expose. With the optional rich-text hook installed, keep writing the same plain-text
dialect below — the hook upgrades it automatically. Do not switch to `##` or `**bold**`.

Section titles + the hook: a title wrapped in box dividers (divider / title / divider)
collapses into a single native header and the divider lines are dropped — they are only the
title signal, never rendered as separator rules. Always pair a divider with a title beneath
it; a lone divider produces nothing. A leading number (`1.`) stays in the header text.

## Governing principle

Technical claim → evidence. Nearly every claim needs a source: `ref:` (official doc),
`commit ref:` (commit), or raw URL of a record/example.

## Content

- **Voice:** first person, active, direct and factual. No greetings, filler, or closings.
- **Peer-to-peer technical:** assume domain knowledge. Explain non-obvious decisions, not basics.
- **Honesty:** document limits, assumptions, and known risks explicitly.
- **Language (mirror context):** English for client/international; Spanish for internal. Match the thread.
- **High detail:** what + how + why, with concrete examples (payloads, IDs, URLs) and the change commit.

## Format

What renders (use):
- Identifiers ALWAYS in backticks: functions `getOptions(productId)`, fields `custbody_acme_synced`,
  records `customrecord_acme_config`, files `client.py`, HTTP verbs `POST`, enums `PACKAGE_DELIVERED`.
- Links: raw URL always. Never `[text](url)` (renders literal).

Plain-text structure (the rest does not render):
- Titles: own line, Title Case, wrapped (divider / title / divider) between
  `────────────────────────────────────────`. Numbered: `1. Title`. The hook collapses the
  block to one header and drops the dividers — never leave a divider without a title beneath it.
- Emphasis/warnings: UPPERCASE (`IMPORTANTE`, `MUST`). NOT `**bold**` (renders literal).
- Labels: own line ending with `:` (`Notas:`, `Approach:`, `Endpoint:`).
- Bullets: `• ` (indent 2). Sub-bullets: `– ` (en dash, indent 4–6).
- Steps: `1.` `2.` `3.` at line start.
- Multi-line snippets: indent 4 spaces per line. NO fences.
- Flows: arrows `→`.
- Refs: own line `ref:` / `commit ref:` / `Doc:` + raw URL.
- Direct someone: tool `assignee` parameter (not `@inline` — does not resolve via API).

## Templates by type

- **A. Work report:** title per component → bullets `•` with `function()` in backticks → `ref:`/`commit ref:` URL.
- **B. Feature/behavior:** divider/numbering → bullets `•` with identifiers → `Notas:` / `IMPORTANTE`.
- **C. API spec:** `Endpoint:` / `Method:` (`POST` in backticks) / `Body:` / `Response:` → indent 4 spaces → realistic example.
- **D. Multi-part plan:** intro → `1. 2. 3.` → owner per step (`-- ALICE`).
- **E. Decision/PoC:** conclusion first → divider → numbered approaches with `Approach:`/`Results:` → `Doc:` URL.
- **F. Quoted content:** clear prefix + indent 4 spaces (not `>`).

## Few-shots

### A — Work report
```
Catalog Service
I added three endpoint calls to the acme-connector catalog REST API.

• `getOptions(productId)` — pulls all product options based on the product ID.
  ref: https://developer.example.com/docs/rest-catalog/product-variant-options/values
• `createVariant(productId, variantData)` — creates a variant and assigns it to a product.
  ref: https://developer.example.com/docs/rest-catalog/product-variants

commit ref: https://github.com/acme-org/acme-connector/commit/abc123def456
```

### B — Feature / behavior documentation
```
────────────────────────────────────────
1. Order creation, update and cancel
────────────────────────────────────────
• Added UserEvent script that runs when a Sales Order is created or edited in the ERP.
• Orders created in the platform have the body field `custbody_acme_synced` marked.

Notas:
• Item maintenance is the client's responsibility (the API offers no method to add items).

IMPORTANTE
We cannot have more than one config record (`customrecord_acme_config`) per account.
